<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./KhymChanur">KhymChanur</a>: ToME 2.2.7 <p>
If I'm in an arena level, there are monsters that I can see (via vision or telepathy) that don't show up on the full-level map. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: Not a bug.  The full level map does not show everything on the level.  It can't; it has to compress in order to fit the full map on screen at once. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./ReenenLaurie">ReenenLaurie</a>: Not 100% sure what the problem is, but I assume when pressing 'M'ap the overhead doesn't show all creatures.  If we start using SDL (3.0.0. or later) you could just change fontsize and display everything.  This would (IMO) be one of the biggest improvements over the current more. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: ASCII can't literally compress. Each ASCII character in the 'M'ap represents several squares of the actual game map. So the 'M'ap shows you where stairs are, store entrances (if any), and a general layout of rooms and corridors (if underground) or of terrain (if in the Wilderness), but the fine detail is lost. 
</p>
</div><div id="footer">


